ocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533950\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 04, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xwa1665702865514.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xwa1665702865514.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xwa1665702865514.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xwa1665702865514\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n       Date and Time Formats in Server Pages\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__date_and_time_formats_in_server_pages_78351\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Date and time formats define the syntax used to display and enter dates and times.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22637e1_d22638e1_d22639e1\">In Uniface desktop applications, a field is formatted according to its display format as soon as the cursor leaves the field. On the web, this is done when a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">webgen</span> (in USPS) or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">websave</span> (in DSPs) statement is executed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22640e1_d22641e1_d22642e1\">For Data and Time fields, the display format is involved in checking the syntax when the cursor leaves the field.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__topic_d16017e1_d16018e1_d16019e1_d16020e1_d16021e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d140923e65\">\n                 \n Date and Time Formats\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22646e1_d22647e1_d22648e1\">Data and time data types in the web environment can be entered with or without separators.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22649e1_d22650e1_d22651e1\">The following table shows some possible display formats and examples. Time and Datetime checking in the web environment differs in behavior from traditional client/server applications.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Date and Time Formats for the Web</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__1\">\n Display format\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__2\">\n Data entered\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__3\">\n Interpretation\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__1\">\n ddmmyy\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__2\">\n 021097\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__3\">\n 2 October 1997\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__1\">\n ddmmmyy\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__2\">\n 02oct1997\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__3\">\n 2 ??? 1997 (month not checked)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__1\">\n ddmmyyyy\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__2\">\n 110197\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__3\">\n 1 October 1997\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__1\">\n ddmmmyyyy\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__2\">\n 2oct97\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__3\">\n 2 ??? 1997 (month not checked)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__1\">\n dd-mm-yy\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__2\">\n 21097\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__3\">\n 2 October 1997\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__1\">\n dd-mmm-yy\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__2\">\n 2Oct97\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__3\">\n 2 ??? 1997 (month not checked)\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__1\">\n dd-mmm-yyyy\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__2\">\n 21097\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__3\">\n 2 October 1997\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__1\">\n ddmmyyyy hhnnss\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__2\">\n 21097 71002\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__3\">\n 2 October 1997 07:10:02\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__1\">\n ddmmyy hh:nn:ss\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__2\">\n 21097 7:10:02\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__3\">\n 2 October 1997 07:10:02\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__1\">\n ddmmyy nn-hh-ss\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__2\">\n 21097 10:07:02\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2573e1_d2574e1_d2575e1__entry__3\">\n 2 October 1997 10:07:02\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22652e1_d22653e1_d22654e1\">Datetime fields allow all date formats and all date plus time formats. When you specify a month using alphabetical rather than numeric characters, for example Oct or October, the month is not checked because the allowed month abbreviations are not known in the web environment. The only check made is that the month name contains at least three characters.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22655e1_d22656e1_d22657e1\">The century depends on the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$CENTURY_BREAK</span> assignment setting and the current century.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__topic_d16022e1_d16023e1_d16024e1_d16025e1_d16026e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d140923e241\">\n                 \n Missing Input\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22661e1_d22662e1_d22663e1\">If a Date, Time, or DateTime field is missing input, Uniface substitutes the following values:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Default Uniface Entries for Missing Input</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__1\">\n Part\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__2\">\n Default\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__1\">\n Day\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__2\">\n 1\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__1\">\n Month\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__2\">\n Current month\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__1\">\n Year\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__2\">\n Current year\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__1\">\n Hour\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__2\">\n 0\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__1\">\n Minute\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__2\">\n 0\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__1\">\n Second\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"xwa1665702865514__table_d2576e1_d2577e1_d2578e1__entry__2\">\n 0\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22664e1_d22665e1_d22666e1\">If a digit is omitted, that is, if the total number of\n            digits entered is not even, or the number of digits in a part is not even, a zero is\n            prefixed to the entry. For example, if you enter <kbd class=\"ph userinput\">11115</kbd> this is\n            considered as <code class=\"ph codeph\">011115</code>, which represents 1 November 1915 (or 2015), not\n            11 November 1905 (or 2005).</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__topic_d16027e1_d16028e1_d16029e1_d16030e1_d16031e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d140923e343\">\n                 \n Separators\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22676e1_d22677e1_d22678e1\">The following characters can be defined as separators:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">~ ’ ! @ # $ ^ ( ) - _ = + { } [ ] | : ; ’ \" &lt; &gt; , . / \n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22679e1_d22680e1_d22681e1\">You can also use the space bar as separators.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22682e1_d22683e1_d22684e1\">When you use separators, leading spaces or zeroes can be omitted from each subsection of a value. For example, you can enter 1 January 1997 as <code class=\"ph codeph\">1-1-97</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22685e1_d22686e1_d22687e1\">You can mix separators, for example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">dd-mmm-yyyy hh:nn:ss</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22688e1_d22689e1_d22690e1\">However, you cannot include more than one separator between each subsection, as in:<code class=\"ph codeph\">dd:-mmm:-yyyy</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xwa1665702865514__p_d22691e1_d22692e1_d22693e1\">If you use:<code class=\"ph codeph\">dd:mmm-yyyy</code> as a format, <code class=\"ph codeph\">10:-yyyy</code> is represented as <code class=\"ph codeph\">10: currentmonth -1997</code>.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533950\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533950\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Date and Time Formats in Server Pages Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 04, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Date and Time Formats in Server Pages Date and time formats define the syntax used to display and enter dates and times. In Uniface desktop applications, a field is formatted according to its display format as soon as the cursor leaves the field. On the web, this is done when a webgen (in USPS) or websave (in DSPs) statement is executed. For Data and Time fields, the display format is involved in checking the syntax when the cursor leaves the field. Date and Time Formats Data and time data types in the web environment can be entered with or without separators. The following table shows some possible display formats and examples. Time and Datetime checking in the web environment differs in behavior from traditional client/server applications. Table 1. Date and Time Formats for the Web Display format Data entered Interpretation ddmmyy 021097 2 October 1997 ddmmmyy 02oct1997 2 ??? 1997 (month not checked) ddmmyyyy 110197 1 October 1997 ddmmmyyyy 2oct97 2 ??? 1997 (month not checked) dd-mm-yy 21097 2 October 1997 dd-mmm-yy 2Oct97 2 ??? 1997 (month not checked) dd-mmm-yyyy 21097 2 October 1997 ddmmyyyy hhnnss 21097 71002 2 October 1997 07:10:02 ddmmyy hh:nn:ss 21097 7:10:02 2 October 1997 07:10:02 ddmmyy nn-hh-ss 21097 10:07:02 2 October 1997 10:07:02 Datetime fields allow all date formats and all date plus time formats. When you specify a month using alphabetical rather than numeric characters, for example Oct or October, the month is not checked because the allowed month abbreviations are not known in the web environment. The only check made is that the month name contains at least three characters. The century depends on the $CENTURY_BREAK assignment setting and the current century. Missing Input If a Date, Time, or DateTime field is missing input, Uniface substitutes the following values: Table 2. Default Uniface Entries for Missing Input Part Default Day 1 Month Current month Year Current year Hour 0 Minute 0 Second 0 If a digit is omitted, that is, if the total number of digits entered is not even, or the number of digits in a part is not even, a zero is prefixed to the entry. For example, if you enter 11115 this is considered as 011115 , which represents 1 November 1915 (or 2015), not 11 November 1905 (or 2005). Separators The following characters can be defined as separators: ~ ’ ! @ # $ ^ ( ) - _ = + { } [ ] | : ; ’ \" < > , . / Copy You can also use the space bar as separators. When you use separators, leading spaces or zeroes can be omitted from each subsection of a value. For example, you can enter 1 January 1997 as 1-1-97 You can mix separators, for example: dd-mmm-yyyy hh:nn:ss However, you cannot include more than one separator between each subsection, as in: dd:-mmm:-yyyy If you use: dd:mmm-yyyy as a format, 10:-yyyy is represented as 10: currentmonth -1997 . Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}